<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12004a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004a"> 4(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cromlech 17 in B / circle of menhirs</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> Enfin les <mark>cromlec&apos;hs, qui sont des menhirs dispos&eacute;s en cercles</mark> plus ou moins r&eacute;guliers <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Ils sont partout tr&egrave;s rares. En dehors du Morbihan et du Finist&egrave;re o&ugrave; l&apos;on en trouve 17, on en conna&icirc;t en France quelques autres; mais, peu nombreux et tr&egrave;s diss&eacute;min&eacute;s, ils ont &eacute;t&eacute;, en g&eacute;n&eacute;ral, fort mal &eacute;tudi&eacute;s et d&eacute;crits. <br><font color="green">[Lastly, the cromlechs, which are <mark>menhirs arranged in more or less regular circles</mark> [&hellip;]</font> These are very rare. Outside Morbihan and <mark>Finist&egrave;re, which has 17 cromlechs</mark>, there are others in France, but they are few and far between. In general, these have been poorly studied and described.] <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Joyce mistook the number of cromlechs in Brittany. </mm> </dd></dl>
